Hi all, new to kerbalism and have come a cross an issue. Currently building station around the mun and on sending some tourists over have noticed a spike in oxygen consumption. The vessel goes from having 9 days of oxygen and a low consumption of 0.01 and then spiking up to 10.24 units and only having a couple of minutes worth of supply. Nitrogen consumption also seems to spike at the same time with a similar jump. As far as I can recreate the scenario it happens on the darkside of the mun or if the vessel is in a particular orientation leading me to think a part is occluded from the sun causing this spike. 

If anyone could guide me as how to check resource consumption on a part by part basis it would be much appreciated.

That's caused by a bug from a previous version that has manifested itself into saves via vessels built in the VAB at the time the bugged version was being used.

Have you tried building a new ship in the VAB with the latest version ?. Note that any vessels saved in the VAB while the bugged version was installed will probably still be bugged when loaded back into the VAB with the latest version. One way to fix a bugged saved VAB vessel is to load in your vessel into the VAB and replace any offending parts, as for those in flight the only way is with a savegame editor.

Hi!

I'm currently trying to create a patch for SSTU ( i know, bad idea).

If i understand correctly, Kerbalism finds parts with crew capacity, calculates volume/surface, and then adds resources to the part (food, water, oxygen, nitrogen, shielding, etc.) depending on the volume (?)

The issue i'm running into is that all habitable parts in SSTU have zero volume in the planner and no resources are added to them (i assume because of the zero volume), then spams the console as it tries to repeatedly pressurize the habitat and fails, again assuming because of the zero volume.

The volume/surface is calculated by kerbalism in part info, and is also displayed in RMB menu in VAB/SPH, but I assume it doesn't get applied to the part for some ungodly reason. Other life support modules (scrubber/pressure control/hum.controller/etc) are working properly.

What i have tried so far (the part is a single part in SSTU that i test on till i figure it out)

This is how SSTU handles USI (roughly, subbed mass for surface) 

@PART[SSTU-ST-DOS-TKS]:FOR[SSTU]:NEEDS[Kerbalism,SSTU]
{
	@MODULE[SSTUModularPart]
	{
		@CORE
		{
			%volume = 24.06
			%surface = 14.68
		}
	}
}

And this is what's used for stock parts in habitat.cfg 

@PART[SSTU-ST-DOS-TKS]:NEEDS[Kerbalism,SSTU]:AFTER[Kerbalism]
{
	@MODULE[Habitat]
	{
		volume = 24.06
		surface = 14.68
	}
}

Tried a variety of FOR, AFTER and FINAL combinations. MM log shows the patch being applied successfully, but alas, the volume in planner is still 0.

included a screenshot for good measure (potato resolution, this is my test install)

Spoiler

https://imgur.com/a/Lss8Eo6#KWz62s9

 

Where am I failing? What am i missing?

My best guess is SSTU somehow overrides volumes set by Kerbalism because of it's containers shenenigans. If so, how do i work around that?

Much appreciated, thank you.

 

EDIT: Found the culprit, it's SSTUVolumeContainer module (their fancy adaptive fuel switch module). i have no idea how to incorporate Kerbalism into it, so I bypassed it by disabling it for now till someone figures out how to make Kerbalism work with it. 

F.
